abstract: The European Commission said on Friday that Booking.com had committed to end "manipulative techniques" on its travel site, such as time-limits for making bookings and misrepresentation of discounts.
snippet: The European Commission said on Friday that Booking.com had committed to end "manipulative techniques" on its travel site, such as time-limits for making bookings and misrepresentation of discounts.
lead_paragraph: BRUSSELS — The European Commission said on Friday that Booking.com had committed to end "manipulative techniques" on its travel site, such as time-limits for making bookings and misrepresentation of discounts.
headline_main: Booking.com Agrees to EU Demands to Change Travel Offers
headline_print_headline: Booking.com Agrees to EU Demands to Change Travel Offers

abstract: The Japanese government has reversed curbs on exports of photoresists to South Korea, one of three technology materials which it had restricted since July, a Trade Ministry official said on Friday.
snippet: The Japanese government has reversed curbs on exports of photoresists to South Korea, one of three technology materials which it had restricted since July, a Trade Ministry official said on Friday.
lead_paragraph: TOKYO/SEOUL — The Japanese government has reversed curbs on exports of photoresists to South Korea, one of three technology materials which it had restricted since July, a Trade Ministry official said on Friday.
headline_main: Japan Partially Reverses Curbs on Tech Materials Exports to South Korea
headline_print_headline: Japan Partially Reverses Curbs on Tech Materials Exports to South Korea

abstract: Only Joe Biden, Pete Buttigieg, Amy Klobuchar, Bernie Sanders and Elizabeth Warren have met the new criteria to take part in the debate, scheduled for Jan. 14 in Des Moines.
snippet: Only Joe Biden, Pete Buttigieg, Amy Klobuchar, Bernie Sanders and Elizabeth Warren have met the new criteria to take part in the debate, scheduled for Jan. 14 in Des Moines.
lead_paragraph: LOS ANGELES — One day after seven candidates took the stage for the most intimate debate of the Democratic presidential primary cycle so far, the Democratic National Committee increased the qualification standards for its next debate in January, making it likely that the field of candidates will be winnowed even further for the event.

abstract: U.S. Chief Justice John Roberts is poised to serve a highly visible though largely ceremonial role in the Senate impeachment trial of President Donald Trump due next month. But it is in his day job on the Supreme Court that the mild-mannered jurist could have a bigger impact on Trump's presidency.
snippet: U.S. Chief Justice John Roberts is poised to serve a highly visible though largely ceremonial role in the Senate impeachment trial of President Donald Trump due next month. But it is in his day job on the Supreme Court that the mild-mannered juris...
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — U.S. Chief Justice John Roberts is poised to serve a highly visible though largely ceremonial role in the Senate impeachment trial of President Donald Trump due next month. But it is in his day job on the Supreme Court that the mild-mannered jurist could have a bigger impact on Trump's presidency.
headline_main: Spotlight Will Be on U.S. Chief Justice in Trump Trial and in Major Cases
headline_print_headline: Spotlight Will Be on U.S. Chief Justice in Trump Trial and in Major Cases

abstract: Putting behind more than three years of tortuous political drama and national division, Parliament voted by a decisive margin to quit the European Union next month.
snippet: Putting behind more than three years of tortuous political drama and national division, Parliament voted by a decisive margin to quit the European Union next month.
lead_paragraph: LONDON — After more than three years of anguished national debate, multiple cliff-hanging votes, and two general elections, Britain’s Parliament voted by a wide margin on Friday to advance Prime Minister Boris Johnson’s Brexit plan, paving the way for the country to leave the European Union next month.

abstract: German Foreign Minister Heiko Maas said Friday he was “under no illusions” that proposed U.S. sanctions against companies involved in building a Russian gas pipeline to Europe might be stopped at the last minute.
snippet: German Foreign Minister Heiko Maas said Friday he was “under no illusions” that proposed U.S. sanctions against companies involved in building a Russian gas pipeline to Europe might be stopped at the last minute.
lead_paragraph: BERLIN — German Foreign Minister Heiko Maas said Friday he was “under no illusions” that proposed U.S. sanctions against companies involved in building a Russian gas pipeline to Europe might be stopped at the last minute.

abstract: U.S. stocks hit record closing highs again on Friday and the S&P 500 registered its biggest weekly percentage gain since early September after data showed a rise in consumer spending and investors continued to be optimistic about developments in the U.S.-China trade dispute.

lead_paragraph: NEW YORK — U.S. stocks hit record closing highs again on Friday and the S&P 500 registered its biggest weekly percentage gain since early September after data showed a rise in consumer spending and investors continued to be optimistic about developments in the U.S.-China trade dispute.
headline_main: S&P 500 Posts Biggest Weekly Percent Gain Since September Amid Data, Trade Optimism

abstract: The 98-year-old husband of Queen Elizabeth II retired from public life in 2017.
snippet: The 98-year-old husband of Queen Elizabeth II retired from public life in 2017.
lead_paragraph: LONDON — Prince Philip, the 98-year-old husband of Queen Elizabeth II of Britain, was taken to a hospital in London on Friday as a precautionary measure to treat a pre-existing condition, Buckingham Palace said in a statement.
